#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code infix ko postfix me convert karne ke liye stack use karta hai.

1. Expression ko left se right traverse karte hain.
2. Agar current character operand ho (letter/number), to directly answer me append kar do.
3. Agar '(' mile, to stack me push kar do.
4. Agar ')' mile, to stack se tab tak operators nikaalo jab tak '(' na mil jaaye.
   Phir '(' ko remove kar do.
5. Agar operator mile (+, -, *, /, ^), to stack ke top par jo operators higher ya equal priority ke hain,
   unhe pehle answer me daal do, fir current operator push karo.
6. End me stack me bache hue sab operators answer me append kar do.

Main idea:
Operands ka order same rehta hai, bas operators ko precedence aur brackets ke according arrange kiya jata hai.
Stack isi precedence handling ke liye use hota hai.

Note:
priority() function operators ki precedence batata hai:
^ > * / > + -

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque;

public class Solution {

    public static int priority(Character a){
      if(a == '^'){
        return 2;
      }
      else if(a == '*' || a == '/'){
        return 1;
      }
      else if(a == '+' || a == '-'){
        return 0;
      }
      else{
        return -1;
      }
    }

    public static String infixToPostfix(String infixExpression) {
      //You can code here

      StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
      int n = infixExpression.length();
      int i = 0;
      Deque<Character> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

      while(i < n){
        //For spaces
        if (infixExpression.charAt(i) == ' ') {
          i++;
          continue;
        }
        //if it is an operand
        if((infixExpression.charAt(i) >= 'A' && infixExpression.charAt(i) <= 'Z') ||
        (infixExpression.charAt(i) >= 'a' && infixExpression.charAt(i) <= 'z') ||
        infixExpression.charAt(i) >= '0' && infixExpression.charAt(i) <= '9'){

          ans.append(infixExpression.charAt(i));
        }

        //if it is an opening bracket
        else if(infixExpression.charAt(i) == '('){
          stack.push(infixExpression.charAt(i));
        }

        //if it is a closing bracket
        else if(infixExpression.charAt(i) == ')'){
          while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() != '('){
            ans.append(stack.pop());
          }
          stack.pop(); //to remove opening bracket from the stack
        }

        //if it is an operator
        else{
          while(!stack.isEmpty()  && stack.peek() != '(' && priority(infixExpression.charAt(i)) <= priority(stack.peek())){
            ans.append(stack.peek());
            stack.pop();
          }
          stack.push(infixExpression.charAt(i));
        }
        i++;
      }

      while(!stack.isEmpty()){
        ans.append(stack.peek());
        stack.pop();
      }

      return ans.toString();
    }
}
